<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mannerly2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mannerly,</orth> adv. decently; civilly: <cit><quote>the wedding m. modest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 79</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>Cupid's post that comes so m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.9.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 9, 100</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>we'll m. demand thee of thy story,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.6.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 6, 92</bibl></cit>.
